Based on your description, it seems you want to destroy an enemy object after a certain amount of time. Here's how you could revise your code:

```cpp
using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Enemy : MonoBehaviour
{
    // The lifetime of the enemy in seconds
    public float enemyLifetime = 6f;

    void Start()
    {
        // Destroy the enemy after 'enemyLifetime' seconds
        Destroy(this.gameObject, enemyLifetime);
    }
}
```

In this code, `Destroy(this.gameObject, enemyLifetime);` will destroy the `Enemy` object itself after `enemyLifetime` seconds. This is a more efficient way as you don't need to update `enemyLifetime` in every frame.

