It seems like you're trying to destroy the enemy game object after a certain amount of time. Here's how you could achieve this:

```csharp
using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Enemy : MonoBehaviour
{
    public float enemyLifetime = 6f;

    void Start()
    {
        Destroy(gameObject, enemyLifetime);
    }
}
```
In the above code, I've used the `Destroy(gameObject, enemyLifetime)` method which destroys the game object after `enemyLifetime` seconds. The `Start()` method ensures that this line of code is executed at the start of the game.

Please note that `Time.deltaTime` is counted in seconds, hence if `enemyLifetime` is set to a value in seconds, it will decrease over time by `Time.deltaTime` seconds in each frame. If you want `enemyLifetime` to be in frames, just remove the `Time.deltaTime` part, the game object will be destroyed after `enemyLifetime` frames.

