Your code has some issues. The first one is that the `Update()` method is empty. You need to fill it with logic, such as movement, rotation, or animation updates. The next problem is that the lifetime is not properly implemented, because `enemyLifetime` is not reset when the enemy is instantiated again. Here is a possible solution:

```csharp
using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Enemy : MonoBehaviour
{
    public float enemyLifetime = 6f;
    private float startTime;

    void Start()
    {
        startTime = Time.time;
    }

    void Update()
    {
        if (Time.time - startTime >= enemyLifetime)
        {
            Destroy(this.gameObject);
        }
    }
}
```

In this code, `startTime` is the time when the `Start()` function is called, and we check if the time elapsed since `startTime` is greater or equal to `enemyLifetime`. If true, we destroy the enemy object. If false, the enemy object will live until `enemyLifetime` seconds have passed from when it was created (`startTime`).

