You are right and I apologize for the confusion. The correct way is to destroy the game object when the lifetime is zero or less than it. 

Here is the fixed code:

```csharp
using System.Collections;
using System.Collections.Generic;
using UnityEngine;

public class Enemy : MonoBehaviour
{
    public float enemyLifetime = 6f;

    void Update()
    {
        enemyLifetime -= Time.deltaTime;
        if (enemyLifetime <= 0f) 
        {
            Destroy(this.gameObject);
        } 
    }
}
```

This code will destroy the enemy object once it's lifetime has expired. The `Time.deltaTime` is used to ensure the lifetime decreases over time, and not all in one go. This way, the enemy object will live for 6 seconds before being destroyed.

